## Engagement Metrics Deep Dive

### 9.1 Core Engagement Metrics and Their Prediction Value

**YouTube's top 4 engagement signals (in algorithmic importance order):**

1. **Average View Duration (AVD)** — 25% of Phase 2 weighting
2. **Total Watch Time** — 40% of Phase 2 weighting (derived from AVD × views)
3. **Viewer Satisfaction** — 35% of Phase 2 weighting
4. **Return Sessions** — 15% of Phase 2 weighting

### 9.2 Engagement Rate Formulas

**Standard Engagement Rate Formula:**

```
ER = (Likes + Comments + Shares + Saves) / Views × 100
```

**Niche-Specific Engagement Rate Benchmarks:**

| Niche | Low ER | Average ER | High ER |
|-------|--------|-----------|---------|
| Gaming | 2% | 5% | 12% |
| Education | 3% | 6% | 15% |
| Entertainment | 2% | 8% | 20% |
| Tech | 1% | 4% | 10% |
| Review | 2% | 6% | 12% |
| Finance | 1% | 3% | 8% |
| Vlog | 3% | 7% | 15% |

### 9.3 Engagement Quality Layers

**YouTube doesn't weight all engagement equally:**

| Engagement Type | Algorithmic Weight | Reason |
|-----------------|-------------------|---------|
| **Likes** | 10% | Easy signal; minimal effort |
| **Comments** | 40% | Indicates deep thought; highest effort |
| **Shares** | 35% | Indicates recommendation behavior; viral signal |
| **Saves** | 15% | Indicates intent to return; loyalty signal |
| **Click-to-subscribe** | +100% (multiplicative bonus) | Explicit channel loyalty |

### 9.4 Timing Impact on Engagement Predictions

**Engagement velocity (speed of accumulation) is a signal:**

- **Fast velocity** (100 likes in first hour): Stronger algorithmic signal
- **Slow velocity** (100 likes over 24 hours): Weaker algorithmic signal

**Predicted Engagement Velocity Formula:**

```
Engagement_Velocity_Multiplier = Early_Engagement (0-6h) / Standard_Expected_Rate
```

**Standard Expected Rates (per hour):**

| Niche | Gaming | Education | Entertainment | Tech | Review | Finance | Vlog |
|-------|--------|-----------|----------------|------|--------|---------|------|
| Per 1K views | 5-15 likes | 4-10 likes | 8-20 likes | 3-8 likes | 4-12 likes | 2-6 likes | 6-16 likes |

